        <label>forsaken crags</label>
        <description>This desertic landscape appears to be perpetually covered in an unnatural fog that seeps all light from the sun. In the ancient past it was partly terraformed by a mysterious humanoid alien race simply known as Forsakens. A plethora of nocturnal alien creatures roam the desert, feeding on bioluminescent plants and fungi that are the only available and reliable source of light.\n\n&lt;color=#AE6233&gt;Biome difficulty: Hard. Luminosity in this biome doesn't reach high enough levels to grow plants, so you'll have to use the flora as natural sunlamps, and all ranged weapons will get a huge penalty. Nights are DARK, and most creatures are nocturnal. Those which aren't, won't last long.&lt;/color&gt;\n\nNOTE: Due to the way vanilla game handles the glow grid, this is unavoidably a laggier biome. Avoid using it with very large modpacks.</description>
